      "The existing 'confirmed order' definition is authoritative and in active use",
      "Teams share vocabulary across the quotes and orders contexts (they are not fully isolated)"
    ]
  },

  "escalations": [
    {
      "type": "contradiction",
      "description": "The term 'confirmed' is being redefined with semantics that directly contradict its established meaning. Existing: confirmed = paid + immutable. Proposed: confirmed = unpaid + mutable. Same word, opposite invariants. This is a ubiquitous language violation that will corrupt the domain model.",
      "affected_stakeholders": ["Sales Agents", "Fulfillment Team", "Finance", "Engineering", "Support"],
      "options": [
